description:
lichen_l2.c:lichen_l2_enable(true) at lines 383-410 duplicates code from lichen_l2_iface_init():

Enable path (383-403):
```c
k_mutex_lock(&tx_mutex, K_FOREVER);
k_mutex_lock(&rx_mutex, K_FOREVER);
if (!atomic_get(&link_ctx_initialized)) {
    const uint8_t *eui64 = lichen_lora_l2_get_eui64();
    // error handling
    secure_zero(&link_ctx, sizeof(link_ctx));
    lichen_link_init(&link_ctx, eui64);
    atomic_set(&link_ctx_initialized, 1);
}
k_mutex_unlock(&rx_mutex);
k_mutex_unlock(&tx_mutex);
lichen_lora_l2_set_rx_callback(lora_rx_callback, NULL);
return lichen_lora_l2_start();
```

Init path (591-606):
```c
lichen_link_init(&link_ctx, eui64);
atomic_set(&link_ctx_initialized, 1);
lichen_iface = iface;
lichen_lora_l2_set_rx_callback(lora_rx_callback, NULL);
```

The enable path has additional mutex handling because it runs post-init. Both paths register the same callback.

What goes wrong: A change to link_ctx initialization (e.g., adding a new field) must be made in two places. The enable path's comment references project-LICHEN-rwio.1 but a reader must find that issue to understand why duplication exists.

Rewrite: Extract a static helper `init_link_ctx_locked(eui64)` called by both paths.
